    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAn extra space is inserted before a function/method, but not before a field when using LSP completion with `clangd`. It doesn't happen with `lua_ls`, though. cc518cf9bab090253b377a87346bdcdead994086 is the first bad commit:\n```\ncommit cc518cf9bab090253b377a87346bdcdead994086\nAuthor: glepnir <glephunter@gmail.com>\nDate:   Sun Mar 22 07:07:26 2026 +0800\n\n    feat(lsp): support CompletionItem.labelDetails #38403\n    \n    Problem: CompletionItem.labelDetails is ignored, losing\n    function signatures and module info in the completion menu.\n    \n    Solution: Append labelDetails.detail to abbr and use\n    labelDetails.description for menu with fallback to item.detail.\n```\n\nMinimal config:\n```\nvim.pack.add {\n  { src = 'https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig', },\n}\n\nvim.lsp.config('lua_ls', {})\nvim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\nvim.lsp.config('clangd', {})\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n```\n\nDemo:\n\n[![asciicast](https://asciinema.org/a/861918.svg)](https://asciinema.org/a/861918)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create config\n```\ncat >~/.config/nvim3/init.lua <<END\nvim.pack.add {\n  { src = 'https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig', },\n}\n\nvim.lsp.config('lua_ls', {})\nvim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\nvim.lsp.config('clangd', {})\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\nEND\n```\n\n2. Edit a c++ file\n```\nNVIM_APPNAME=nvim3 nvim test.cpp\n```\n\n3. Try completing `std::cout.<c-x><c-o>`\n4. Witness a space is prepended\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo space is prepended before a method name, like before the change.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2664+g256811a617\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.46.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
