            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I also saw something like a middle dot prepended during completion. But I can't remember how to reproduce it.\n\nI can reproduce the dot with:\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\nint main() {\n\tstd::|\n\treturn 0;\n}\n```\n\n<img width=\"1468\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/06a7c946-b442-44ef-9bf0-30bc0c90bd16\" />\n\nclangd sometimes prepend it to indicate something (no idea what). And looking at the LSP logs, it sends space instead of dot, probably so that all items are aligned in completion menu.\n\n```\n{ detail = \"__ostream_type &\", filterText = \"flush\", insertText = \"flush()\", insertTextFormat = 2, kind = 2, label = \" flush\", labelDetails = { detail = \"()\" }, score = 0.93680763244629, sortText = \"40902d60flush\", textEdit = { newText = \"flush()\", range = { [\"end\"] = { character = 11, line = 3 }, start = { character = 11, line = 3 } } } }\n```\n\nProbably Nvim should compute the displayed string differently, or trim it.",
