            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "clangd consistently inserts a specific character before labels to serve as an alignment indicator: a bullet point (•) is used when an `#include` needs to be inserted, while a space is used otherwise.\n\nhttps://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/3011d68a7810ff25653c33ff0389fae9413a26a7/clang-tools-extra/clangd/CodeComplete.cpp#L2403-L2407\n\ndefinition in CodeComplete.h\n\n```C\n  /// A visual indicator to prepend to the completion label to indicate whether\n  /// completion result would trigger an #include insertion or not.\n  struct IncludeInsertionIndicator {\n    std::string Insert = \"•\";\n    std::string NoInsert = \" \";\n  } IncludeIndicator;\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-03-23T12:11:12Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38433#issuecomment-4110160580",
